                                <p style='font-size:13px;text-align:center;'><strong><span style=''>(For Nursing, Paramedics &amp; Support Staff)</span></strong></p>
                                <p style='font-size:13px;text-align:justify;'><strong><em><span style=''>&nbsp;</span></em></strong></p>
                                <p style='font-size:13px;text-align:justify;'><strong><span style=''>Employees&rsquo; Health BenefitScheme:</span></strong></p>
                                <ul style="list-style-type: disc;margin-left:26px;">
                                    <li><span style=''>Being an employee of <strong>Dr. Prabhat Memorial Hiramati Hospital</strong>you will be eligible for Employees&rsquo; Health BenefitScheme.&nbsp;</span></li>
                                    <li><span style=''>All staff members &amp; their dependents (parents, spouse and dependent children) are eligible for confessional treatment at <strong>Dr. Prabhat Memorial Hiramati Hospital</strong>.</span></li>
                                </ul>
                                <p style='font-size:13px;margin-left:36.0pt;text-align:justify;'><span style=''>&nbsp;</span></p>
                                <p style='font-size:13px;text-align:justify;'><strong><span style=''>ProvidentFund:</span></strong></p>
                                <ul style="list-style-type: disc;margin-left:26px;">
                                    <li><span style=''>You will be a member of the Provident Fund as per the provisions under &ldquo;TheEmployees Provident Fund (EPF) and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952&rdquo;, andthecontribute&nbsp;details towards EPF has been mentioned on your Compensation details.&nbsp;</span></li>
                                    <li><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Tax exception can be claimed for PF amount deposited u/s &ndash; 80C. &nbsp;</span></li>
                                    <li><span style=''>You are required to submit your Universal Account Number (UAN), if any, issued by your previous employer on the Declaration Form (Form 9) so as to link your UAN with DRL PF / Pension account.</span></li>
                                </ul>
                                <p style='font-size:13px;text-align:justify;'><span style=''>&nbsp;</span></p>
                                <p style='font-size:13px;text-align:justify;'><strong><span style=''>Employees&apos;PensionScheme:</span></strong></p>
                                <div style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:13px;'>
                                    <ul style="margin-bottom:0cm;list-style-type: disc;margin-left:26px;">
                                        <li style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:13px;'><span style=''>Your enrolment under the Employees&rsquo; Pension Scheme (EPS) will based on thedetails you provide under the Declaration Form (Form 9) at the time ofjoiningDRL Multispecialty Hospital.</span></li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                                <p style='font-size:13px;text-align:justify;'><strong><span style=''>&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
                                <p style='font-size:13px;text-align:justify;'><strong><span style=''>ESIC </span></strong></p>
                                <ul style="list-style-type: disc;margin-left:26px;">
                                    <li><span style=''>As per the Employees&rsquo; State Insurance (ESIC) Act, all employees whose Gross is less than &amp; equal to Rs.21000/- per month come under the preview of the act andthecontribute&nbsp;details towards ESI has been mentioned on your Compensation details.&nbsp;</span></li>
                                    <li><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>Eligible employee may avail Medical Benefit, Sickness Benefit, Maternity Benefit, Disablement Benefit, Un-employment Allowances &amp; Dependents&rsquo; Benefit under ESIC.</span></li>
                                </ul>
                                <p style='font-size:13px;text-align:justify;'><span style=''>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>
                                <p style='font-size:13px;text-align:justify;'><strong><span style=''>Gratuity&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
                                <div style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:13px;'>
                                    <ul style="margin-bottom:0cm;list-style-type: disc;margin-left:26px;">
                                        <li style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:13px;'><span style=''>You will be entitled to gratuity as per the provisions of the Gratuity Act 1972. Staff members who complete a continuous service of five years or more would are eligible for gratuity as per the Payment of Gratuity Act.</span></li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                                <p style='font-size:13px;text-align:justify;'><strong><span style=''>&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
                                <p style='font-size:13px;text-align:justify;'><strong><span style=''>Holidays</span></strong></p>
                                <ul style="list-style-type: disc;margin-left:26px;">
                                    <li><span style='font-size:10.0pt;'>PH &amp; RH would be applicable&nbsp;</span><span style=''>for all regular employee, which will be released in every calendar year.&nbsp;</span></li>
                                    <li><span style=''>RH can be availed only after completion of three months from your date of joining.&nbsp;</span></li>
                                </ul>
                                <p style='font-size:13px;margin-left:36.0pt;text-align:justify;'><strong><span style=''>&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
                                <p style='font-size:13px;text-align:justify;'><strong><span style=''>Leave</span></strong></p>
                                <ul class="decimal_type" style="list-style-type: disc;margin-left:26px;">
                                    <li><span style='font-size:10.0pt;color:red;'>You are eligible for leave benefit under&nbsp;</span><strong><span style=''>Dr. Prabhat Memorial Hiramati Hospital</span></strong><span style="font-size:10.0pt;color:red;">&nbsp;leave policy. &nbsp;Leave is a privilege which can be availed only post necessary approval. Total 21 PL, 12 CL &amp; 9 SL&nbsp;</span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;color:red;'>to be credited in a FY on pro rata basis</span><span style='color:red;'>.&nbsp;</span></li>
                                    <li><span style='font-size:10.0pt;color:red;'>3 CL can be availed at a stretch post completion of three months from joining. Un-availed CL will be lapsed at the end of every FY.</span></li>
                                    <li><span style='font-size:10.0pt;color:red;'>Min. 4 PL &amp; maximum 21 PL can be availed at a stretch post completion of six months from joining. Upto 42 unvailed PL can be en-cashable at the time of full and final settlement. However, it will be applicable for the regular employees&rsquo; (other than Clinicians) only post completion of one year of service.</span></li>
                                    <li><span style='font-size:10.0pt;color:red;'>Upto 18 SL can be accumulated at a stretch. However, Medical certificate &amp; Fitness Certificate is mandatory to regularize more than 3 SL.&nbsp;</span></li>
                                    <li><span style='font-size:10.0pt;color:red;'>Women employees are eligible to avail maternity leave (ML) of twenty-six weeks as per the Maternity Benefit Act,1961 &amp; Maternity Benefit (Amendment) Act. For more details on the benefits and eligibility, please refer to DRL Leave Policy</span></li>
                                </ul>
                                <p style='font-size:13px;text-align:justify;'><strong><span style=''>Attendance&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></strong></p>
                                <ul style="list-style-type: disc;margin-left:26px;">
                                    <li><span style=''>You are required to record your attendance in the biometric machine / signing in the attendance register provided or as advised from time to time by HR Dept.</span></li>
                                    <li><span style=''>Absence needs to be informed to the HOD, and prior permission sought from him/her, preferably in advance.&nbsp;</span></li>
                                </ul>
